modules.description: Loads environment variables from a `.env` file and injects them into `Sys.env` for runtime access. Works with string-based key-value pairs parsed from text files. Enables local development setups to mirror production configurations without hardcoding values.

Reads and processes environment variables from a file using specified encoding, returning key-value pairs for program configuration. Injects parsed variables into the system environment for runtime access by external processes. Supports multiple character encodings including UTF-8 and UTF-16 variants.
